com.microsoft.windowsazure.management.configuration

Class PublishSettingsLoader

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.microsoft.windowsazure.management.configuration.PublishSettingsLoader

  • public abstract class PublishSettingsLoader
extends Object
    Loading a publish settings file to create a service management configuration. Supports both schema version 1.0 (deprecated) and 2.0. To get different schema versions, use the 'SchemaVersion' query parameter when downloading the file:
    • https://manage.windowsazure.com/publishsettings/Index?client=vs& SchemaVersion=1.0
    • https://manage.windowsazure.com/publishsettings/Index?client=vs& SchemaVersion=2.0

    • Method Detail

      • createManagementConfiguration

        public static Configuration createManagementConfiguration(String publishSettingsFileName,
                                                          String subscriptionId)
                                                   throws IOException
        Create a service management configuration using specified publish settings file and subscription ID.

        Please note:

        • Will use the first PublishProfile present in the file.
        • An unprotected keystore file keystore.out will be left in the working directory containing the management certificate.
        Parameters:
        publishSettingsFileName - The name of the publish settings file with a valid certificate obtained from Microsoft Azure portal.
        subscriptionId - subscription ID
        Returns:
        a management configuration instance
        Throws:
        IOException - if any error occurs when handling the specified file or the keystore
        IllegalArgumentException - if the file is not of the expected format
